<subSubSection id="88DE6550FFB5FFDA0F9CB92EC340F914" pageId="23" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C07B36DBFFB5FFDA0F9CB92EC340F914" blockId="23.[160,1156,1599,1727]" pageId="23" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="F2B0EAC9FFB5FFDA0F9CB92EC3E2F9FC" bold="true" box="[160,423,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="297">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna serrate; posterior corners of pronotum obtuse; sterna VI with a circular lantern, VII usually with a circular lantern, VIII with posterior margin with an acute median projection. Dorsal colour pattern: overall black, with a longitudinal pale yellow stripe on elytra.
</paragraph>
